    <oval-def:description>It was discovered that the Dovecot email server is vulnerable to a denial of service attack. When the 'dict' passdb and userdb are used for user authentication,
		the username sent by the IMAP/POP3 client is sent through var_expand() to perform %variable expansion.
		Sending specially crafted %variable fields could result in excessive memory usage causing the process to crash (and restart).</oval-def:description>
